    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>No, there is no better way.</p>\n\n<p>Actually you have an error in your pattern. What you want is:</p>\n\n<pre><code>DecimalFormat df = new DecimalFormat(\"#.00\"); \n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Note the <code>\"00\"</code>, meaning <em>exactly</em> two decimal places.</p>\n\n<p>If you use <code>\"#.##\"</code> (<code>#</code> means \"optional\" digit), it will drop trailing zeroes - ie <code>new DecimalFormat(\"#.##\").format(3.0d);</code> prints just <code>\"3\"</code>, not <code>\"3.00\"</code>.</p>\n"
  }, {
