    "body" : "<p>An alternative is to use <code>String.format</code>:</p>\n\n<pre><code>double[] arr = { 23.59004,\n    35.7,\n    3.0,\n    9\n};\n\nfor ( double dub : arr ) {\n  System.out.println( String.format( \"%.2f\", dub ) );\n}\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>output:</p>\n\n<pre><code>23.59\n35.70\n3.00\n9.00\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>You could also use <code>System.out.format</code> (same method signature), or create a <code>java.util.Formatter</code> which works in the same way.</p>\n"
  } ],
